SIMPLE: sameness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sameness
<hw>Same"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being
the same; identity; absence of difference; near resemblance;
correspondence; similarity; <as>as, a <ex>sameness</ex> of person, of
manner, of sound, of appearance, and the like</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>sameness</xex> of the terms.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp.
Horsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, want of variety; tedious monotony.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Identity; identicalness; oneness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Samette</ent>⟦br⟧
